[38.417355, "o", "Done! I've created all three Frame-phase artifacts for hello-helix:\r\n\r\n✅ **docs/helix/00-discover/product-vision.md** (25 lines)\r\n   - Mission: simple, reliable CLI temperature conversion\r\n   - Target: developers in terminal workflows\r\n   - Scope and success criteria defined\r\n\r\n✅ **docs/helix/01-frame/prd.md** (49 lines)\r\n   - Core features: `--to-celsius` and `--to-fahrenheit` flags\r\n   - Output format: one decimal place precision\r\n   - Three-tier priorities: P0 (basic), P1 (errors), P2 (batch mode)\r\n\r\n✅ **docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-001-temperature-conversion.md** (43 lines)\r\n   - Three user stories with concrete acceptance criteria\r\n   - 212°F → 100.0°C, 0°C → 32.0°F, 98.6°F → 37.0°C\r\n   - Supports decimal input and negative numbers\r\n\r\nThe directory structure is in place and ready for the Specification and Design phases.\r\n\r\n"]
[41.419345, "o", "  ✓ vision exists\r\n  ✓ PRD exists\r\n"]
[41.419424, "o", "── docs/helix/00-discover/product-vision.md ──\r\n"]
[41.421395, "o", "# Product Vision: hello-helix\r\n\r\n## Mission\r\nProvide a simple, reliable temperature conversion tool accessible from the command line—enabling developers to convert between Celsius and Fahrenheit instantly without leaving their terminal.\r\n\r\n## Target Audience\r\nDevelopers and engineers who:\r\n- Work regularly in terminal environments (scripts, automation, data pipelines)\r\n- Need quick temperature conversions during development or debugging\r\n- Prefer CLI tools over web interfaces or calculator apps\r\n\r\n## Value Proposition\r\n- **Speed**: Convert in one command, no UI overhead\r\n- **Reliability**: Accurate conversions with consistent output format\r\n"]
[41.421443, "o", "- **Simplicity**: Single, focused purpose—temperature conversion\r\n"]
[41.42174, "o", "...\r\n\r\n"]
[43.424379, "o", "── docs/helix/01-frame/prd.md ──\r\n"]
[43.427089, "o", "# Product Requirements Document: hello-helix\r\n\r\n## Overview\r\nA Node.js CLI tool for converting temperatures between Celsius and Fahrenheit.\r\n\r\n## Core Features\r\n\r\n### Convert to Celsius\r\n```\r\nconvert --to-celsius <temperature>\r\n```\r\nConverts Fahrenheit to Celsius.\r\n\r\n### Convert to Fahrenheit\r\n```\r\nconvert --to-fahrenheit <temperature>\r\n```\r\nConverts Celsius to Fahrenheit.\r\n\r\n## Output Format\r\n"]
[43.427166, "o", "...\r\n\r\n"]
